<p>Before I got to the final mocks, I went through multiple iterations just on the landing page. It was crucial for me to understand the priority and hierarchy of the pages. Initially, I made something very similar to Doodle. It had a series of welcoming, tutorial, and set up pages until the actual poll page. At the time, I believed it was important to have a solid onboarding process to use the product and therefore the product became unnecessarily complicated. Then I realized Yogo should be simple enough that it does not need any onboarding process. Ultimately, I gutted away all the other pages but the poll page itself.</p>

